docs.abstract: Popular novels, technical tomes and self-published books are pirated and sold on Amazon. That may actually be helping the company extend its grip on the book business.

docs.lead_paragraph: SPERRYVILLE, Va. — “The Sanford Guide to Antimicrobial Therapy” is a medical handbook that recommends the right amount of the right drug for treating ailments from bacterial pneumonia to infected wounds. Lives depend on it.

docs.abstract: Has music streaming ignored aficionados of Mozart and Beethoven? Two new services, Idagio and Primephonic, address the needs of the genre’s discerning listeners.
docs.snippet: Has music streaming ignored aficionados of Mozart and Beethoven? Two new services, Idagio and Primephonic, address the needs of the genre’s discerning listeners.
docs.lead_paragraph: When Roopa Kalyanaraman Marcello, a classical music aficionado in Brooklyn, asked her Amazon Echo for some music recently, she had a specific request: the third movement of Beethoven’s “Emperor” Concerto.

headline.main: In Streaming Age, Classical Music Gets Lost in the Metadata
headline.print_headline: Classical Fans Trying to Stream Search in Vain

docs.abstract: The company acquiring the bimonthly fashion title, which also owns Surface and Watch Journal, named Sara Moonves, the current style director, as W’s next editor in chief.
docs.snippet: The company acquiring the bimonthly fashion title, which also owns Surface and Watch Journal, named Sara Moonves, the current style director, as W’s next editor in chief.
docs.lead_paragraph: The magazine giant Condé Nast said on Tuesday that it had found a buyer for the bimonthly fashion title W, one of three publications the company put up for sale last year in the face of significant financial losses that forced it to adopt a series of cost-cutting measures.

headline.main: Condé Nast Sells W Magazine; Stefano Tonchi Out as Top Editor
headline.print_headline: Condé Nast Finds Buyer for W Magazine

docs.abstract: The world’s largest drone maker is the latest Chinese technology company scrambling to retain their ability to sell to the United States.
docs.snippet: The world’s largest drone maker is the latest Chinese technology company scrambling to retain their ability to sell to the United States.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — DJI, the large Chinese drone maker, is facing mounting security concerns within the Trump administration that its flying machines could send sensitive surveillance data back to China. Now, the company is trying to get on American officials’ good side by building some products in the United States.

headline.main: Chinese Drones Made in America: One Company’s Plan to Win Over Trump
headline.print_headline: Hoping to Win Trust, DJI Will Build Drone in U.S.

docs.abstract: The presidents of the St. Louis and Minneapolis branches of the Federal Reserve want rates cut now, and even the central bank’s vice chair says uncertainty is growing.
docs.snippet: The presidents of the St. Louis and Minneapolis branches of the Federal Reserve want rates cut now, and even the central bank’s vice chair says uncertainty is growing.
docs.lead_paragraph: Federal Reserve officials on Friday outlined the case for an interest-rate cut, making clear in their first public remarks since the central bank chose to leave policy unchanged this week that inflation and rising global risks are weighing heavily on their minds.
